SIMPLE: eunomian
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eunomian
<hw>Eu*no"mi*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl.
Hist.)</fld> <def>A follower of <persfn>Eunomius</persfn>, bishop of
Cyzicus (4th century <sc>A. D.</sc>), who held that Christ was not God
but a created being, having a nature different from that of the
Father.</def> -- <def2><pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to
<persfn>Eunomius</persfn> or his doctrine.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eunomy</ent>⟦br⟧
